results.deck: Primarily known for publishing popular family board games, Parker also released quite a few computer games between the early 1980s and early 1990s.
results.description: Traditional board game publisher Parker Brother's first endeavour on the video game market happened in the year 1982. They produced a few original titles but the majority of their output were license of arcade games and ports from various other systems. Initially, Parker released game on console systems  Atari 2600, Odyssey 2, Intellivision, Atari 5200, and ColecoVision but would later also release games for home computer systems such as the C64.
